00:01:40.595 --> 00:01:46.255
any element regardless of how deep it is in the layer structure.

00:01:46.255 --> 00:01:52.415
For the heading, we're going to change its color to white.

00:01:52.415 --> 00:01:55.320
Then we're going to go back to

00:01:55.320 --> 00:02:01.250
our typography and we're going to use the style of Heading 1.

00:02:01.250 --> 00:02:05.675
Now, you can glance over these values

00:02:05.675 --> 00:02:11.560
and commit them to memory and then replicate them on the other side,

00:02:11.560 --> 00:02:15.285
or you can right-click, go to Copy/Paste,

00:02:15.285 --> 00:02:19.940
Copy Properties, and then you can come back to main design,

00:02:19.940 --> 00:02:23.935
right-click, Copy/Paste, Paste Properties.

00:02:23.935 --> 00:02:28.050
That will change everything,

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:30.575
the font family, weight,

00:02:30.575 --> 00:02:33.935
the font size, the line height, all of it.

00:02:33.935 --> 00:02:42.110
Now all we have to do is basically change the color back and let's bring up the grid,

00:02:42.110 --> 00:02:44.390
let's align this to the grid,

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:48.780
and we're going to change the width of

00:02:48.780 --> 00:02:55.575
this element so that it spans on seven columns.

00:02:55.575 --> 00:02:57.870
We have 1, 2, 3,

00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:00.345
4, 5, 6, 7.

00:03:00.345 --> 00:03:03.210
Next, let's target this bit.

00:03:03.210 --> 00:03:11.720
For this, let's go back to typography and select a style that would work best for us.

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:16.455
In our case, we'll probably be using Heading 5.

00:03:16.455 --> 00:03:19.320
Right click, Copy/Paste, Copy Properties,

00:03:19.320 --> 00:03:23.940
go back and Paste Properties.

00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:29.060
Now, this doesn't really work that well in medium,

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:30.800
so let's switch back to regular.

00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:33.875
You can make these changes, no problem.

00:03:33.875 --> 00:03:41.075
Let's resize this as well and let's actually change to auto width.

00:03:41.075 --> 00:03:47.945
That means the text box will resize to the maximum width of the text inside it.

00:03:47.945 --> 00:03:51.620
Let's switch its color to white,

00:03:51.620 --> 00:03:55.845
and let's use a more subdued tint,

00:03:55.845 --> 00:03:58.020
60 percent, let's say.

00:03:58.020 --> 00:04:00.860
Awesome. We're making great progress.

00:04:00.860 --> 00:04:03.215
Now, let's look at this button.

00:04:03.215 --> 00:04:08.970
For this button, I want the text to say, download for free,

00:04:08.970 --> 00:04:16.820
but I would also like a nice arrow to sit right next to it.

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:21.649
I'm going to show you an amazing way of creating buttons in Figma

00:04:21.649 --> 00:04:28.520
that allows you to type any text you want in them and they'll resize automatically.

00:04:28.520 --> 00:04:35.035
That's with the help of our trusty friend auto layout.

00:04:35.035 --> 00:04:41.024
What I'm going to do is select the text itself,

00:04:41.024 --> 00:04:47.130
and I'm actually going to move this outside,

00:04:47.570 --> 00:04:50.445
and I'm going to ungroup this.

00:04:50.445 --> 00:04:51.840
With the Text selected,

00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:54.440
press ''Shift+A'' to add auto layout,

00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:57.140
and I'm going to select 32 pixels,

00:04:57.140 --> 00:05:00.304
horizontal padding, 16 pixels,

00:05:00.304 --> 00:05:04.880
vertical padding, and 16 pixels spacing between items.

00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:12.630
Now what I can do is I can add a fill color and I'm going to add fill white 100 percent.

00:05:12.630 --> 00:05:19.355
I'm also going to add a 100 pixel corner radius.

00:05:19.355 --> 00:05:21.350
Do you know why I did that?

00:05:21.350 --> 00:05:25.625
Because if we're going to take a look at the project brief,

00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:29.240
under design considerations, the client tells us that,

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:33.455
"Hey, we like pill and ghost buttons."

00:05:33.455 --> 00:05:37.760
A pill button is the one with very rounded corners.

00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:40.135
It looks like an actual pill.

00:05:40.135 --> 00:05:48.875
With that done, I can select the text inside it and I can set it to my primary color.

00:05:48.875 --> 00:05:50.824
Let's go to Colors,

00:05:50.824 --> 00:05:56.685
select my primary, let's come back and paste it in.

00:05:56.685 --> 00:05:59.690
Now as far as the text is concerned,

00:05:59.690 --> 00:06:03.655
we're going to use Brandon Grotesque.

00:06:03.655 --> 00:06:07.535
Let me actually zoom in here.

00:06:07.535 --> 00:06:11.334
We're going to use bold 18 pixels,

00:06:11.334 --> 00:06:14.400
24 for line height,

00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:16.965
and we should be good to go.

00:06:16.965 --> 00:06:22.520
Now, I'm also going to add a drop shadow to it.

00:06:22.520 --> 00:06:24.350
I'm going to select my frame,

00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:27.285
which I'm going to call Button,

00:06:27.285 --> 00:06:32.100
and under effects, I'm going to choose Drop shadow.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:36.260
The same one that we used for these elements here.

00:06:36.260 --> 00:06:41.765
The last thing that we need to do here is to add a nice arrow.

00:06:41.765 --> 00:06:47.115
For that, I'm going to go to my app here,

00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:49.035
I'm going to search for arrow,

00:06:49.035 --> 00:06:54.630
and we're going to choose the arrow right from the Microns set.

00:06:54.630 --> 00:06:59.025
So click and drag and drop it in.

00:06:59.025 --> 00:07:05.475
Here, we're going to keep it at 24 pixels and I'm going to hit ''Command+X.''

00:07:05.475 --> 00:07:11.465
I'm going to select this text and Command+V+V or Control+V for on Windows.

00:07:11.465 --> 00:07:18.915
This is going to paste it right next to that text inside my button frame.

00:07:18.915 --> 00:07:25.300
All I got to do now is change the color to the same color as the text.

00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:29.215
Here, I'm going to give you another pro tip.

00:07:29.215 --> 00:07:31.180
When working in Figma,

00:07:31.180 --> 00:07:34.510
and you want to change the color on multiple elements,

00:07:34.510 --> 00:07:40.660
you can select the parent element and when you see selection colors,

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:47.090
this will basically give you the colors of every single element in that selection.

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:54.160
If I want to change the color of this arrow to the color of this text,

00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:56.770
all I got to do is copy the color of the text,

00:07:56.770 --> 00:08:01.065
paste it in, and I'm good to go.

00:08:01.065 --> 00:08:04.770
Now our button is complete,

00:08:04.770 --> 00:08:08.530
and because I'm using auto layout,

00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:12.139
I can change the text on this button,

00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:17.515
like so and the button will resize automatically.

00:08:17.515 --> 00:08:19.225
How cool is that?

00:08:19.225 --> 00:08:27.430
Of course, I can also change the padding and the distance between items.

00:08:27.430 --> 00:08:34.400
I can do this, and I can do this.

00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:43.620
I can do this. Well, that was a very large value, but you get the point.

00:08:43.620 --> 00:08:50.040
I get very fine control over how this looks like and it's super easy to use.

00:08:50.040 --> 00:08:54.045
Now, let's see about this video introduction link.

00:08:54.045 --> 00:08:59.340
For it, I'm going to be using my secondary color.

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:01.995
Let's select that, copy it,

00:09:01.995 --> 00:09:05.790
paste it in, type face.

00:09:05.790 --> 00:09:08.670
We're going to use Brandon Grotesque again,

00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:14.220
18, 24 and Bold.

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:18.855
The last thing to do is add a little icon to it as well,

00:09:18.855 --> 00:09:22.545
because I wanted to show the fact that,

00:09:22.545 --> 00:09:26.010
hey, if you click this link a video is going to play.

00:09:26.010 --> 00:09:29.760
So we need an icon that says play.

00:09:29.760 --> 00:09:35.100
We have this one or if we go to Ionicons,

00:09:35.100 --> 00:09:38.790
we will get this one.

00:09:38.790 --> 00:09:44.970
Drag and drop. I'm going to resize to 24,

00:09:44.970 --> 00:09:52.950
like so and I'm going to select the icon and the text.

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:57.565
I'm going to press "Shift + A" to create an auto layout.

00:09:57.565 --> 00:09:59.930
Now, when doing this,

00:09:59.930 --> 00:10:05.135
you can align elements in a number of different ways.

00:10:05.135 --> 00:10:08.915
If the auto layout was horizontal,

00:10:08.915 --> 00:10:15.300
you can align elements at the top, center, or bottom.

00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:18.810
If your auto layout is set to vertical,

00:10:18.810 --> 00:10:24.525
you can align elements left, center, and right.

00:10:24.525 --> 00:10:27.250
This is what it's doing.

00:10:30.440 --> 00:10:38.440
You can also choose to move up an element or move down.

00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:43.020
Of course, if the layout is in horizontal mode,

00:10:43.020 --> 00:10:46.665
you can move elements left and right.

00:10:46.665 --> 00:10:52.020
You can also use the keyboard shortcuts left, right, top, bottom.

00:10:52.020 --> 00:10:55.020
In my case, I'm going to choose to align

00:10:55.020 --> 00:11:01.930
this icon in the middle and also this text in the middle.

00:11:02.330 --> 00:11:05.820
As for distance between items,

00:11:05.820 --> 00:11:08.325
I'm going to choose 16 pixels.

00:11:08.325 --> 00:11:16.635
I'm going to make sure that I am using the same color on this icon.

00:11:16.635 --> 00:11:24.645
Now what you can do is you can group up these two elements with auto layout.

00:11:24.645 --> 00:11:31.515
You can press "Shift + A" and that's going to create another frame for both of them.

00:11:31.515 --> 00:11:37.200
It can set its spacing between items to 32.

00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:42.255
By default, this will align these elements in the middle.

00:11:42.255 --> 00:11:47.535
Now, I want the same distance between these three elements.

00:11:47.535 --> 00:11:52.215
What I can do is I can select all of them by holding down "Shift".

00:11:52.215 --> 00:11:56.400
I can do "Shift + A" to add auto-layout.

00:11:56.400 --> 00:12:02.970
I'm simply going to change the distance between them or the spacing between them to 32.

00:12:02.970 --> 00:12:11.520
Also, I'm going to make sure that all of these are aligned to the left. Like so.

00:12:11.520 --> 00:12:15.855
Now the last thing to do is to position this content at

00:12:15.855 --> 00:12:20.910
a respectable distance from the header.

00:12:20.910 --> 00:12:23.250
In our case it's 96 pixels,

00:12:23.250 --> 00:12:26.385
which incidentally is a multiple of eight.

00:12:26.385 --> 00:12:29.355
I'm actually going to keep this positioning.

00:12:29.355 --> 00:12:32.114
But if you want to position it differently,

00:12:32.114 --> 00:12:38.115
you would use the up and down arrow keys.

00:12:38.115 --> 00:12:44.519
Cool. Now, this is the first part of the content.

00:12:44.519 --> 00:12:50.190
The last part is to add this media object.

00:12:50.190 --> 00:12:52.935
Here's how we'll go about that.

00:12:52.935 --> 00:12:55.560
We're going to start by creating

00:12:55.560 --> 00:13:00.180
a simple shape and we're going to add a border radius of 8,

00:13:00.180 --> 00:13:03.880
a height of 240 pixels.

