That's because when you're adding or when you're creating a frame with auto layout,

00:18:55.060 --> 00:19:00.520
it usually will check out this box where it says clip content

00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:07.450
and that will basically clip any content that is outside the boundaries of that frame.

00:19:07.450 --> 00:19:11.469
In our case, the shadow is outside the boundaries.

00:19:11.469 --> 00:19:22.195
I can uncheck this and then we can go in even deeper and uncheck this box and now,

00:19:22.195 --> 00:19:26.030
see how the shadow's showing up.

00:19:27.240 --> 00:19:34.690
This is something you can do when you see this happening.

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:39.070
When an image that should be outside the bounds of

00:19:39.070 --> 00:19:44.410
your frame doesn't show up usually this is the culprit right here.

