All right, there's one final small thing that we need to do here.

00:19:50.605 --> 00:20:00.460
Right here at the bottom we're going to add a little icon that will let users know that,

00:20:00.460 --> 00:20:02.875
'hey, you can scroll down this page.'

00:20:02.875 --> 00:20:07.165
To create that start with a rectangle.

00:20:07.165 --> 00:20:12.430
We're going to set its width to 24, it's height to 48,

00:20:12.430 --> 00:20:15.520
its radius to 100,

00:20:15.520 --> 00:20:17.650
and we're actually going to remove

00:20:17.650 --> 00:20:21.535
the fill color and we're going to add a stroke or a border,

00:20:21.535 --> 00:20:24.430
and the border is going to be white.

00:20:24.430 --> 00:20:30.310
It's going to be inside one pixel and then inside that

00:20:30.310 --> 00:20:36.445
we're going to create a nice circle using the ellipse tool.

00:20:36.445 --> 00:20:41.980
When using the ellipse tool we can free hand it or we can hold down

00:20:41.980 --> 00:20:47.830
shift and it's going to snap to the same width and height.

00:20:47.830 --> 00:20:51.325
Let's make this very small,

00:20:51.325 --> 00:20:53.545
six by six should do the trick.

00:20:53.545 --> 00:21:02.020
Fill white, and then just move it inside my little icon here.

00:21:02.020 --> 00:21:05.545
You can set it at eight pixels from the top.

00:21:05.545 --> 00:21:06.940
That should do the trick.

00:21:06.940 --> 00:21:10.420
Select both, command G to group them all together,

